term_definitions.items: Дополнительная контекстная информация для хранения в Context_details
Для описания срока действия назначений и направлений
*Length of time the referral is valid.(en)
*Duration for which the referral is valid.(en)
*If true, referral is for an indefinite period of time.(en)
*A list of people or organisations who are relevant to this referral, including next of kin.(en)
*Generic request for a range of different healthcare services e.g referral, lab request, equipment request.(en)
Запрос на оказание конкретной услуги другим медицинским учреждением или организацией.
*The local ID assigned to the order by the healthcare provider or organisation requesting the service. This is also referred to as Placer Order Identifier.(en)
*The ID assigned to the order by the healthcare provider or organisation receiving the request for service. This is also referred to as Filler Order Identifier.(en)
*The date and time that the service should be performed or completed.(en)
*A short description of the reason for the request. This is often coded with an external terminology.(en)
*A narrative description explaining the reason for request.(en)
*Stated intent of the request by the referrer.(en)
*True indicates that additional information has been identified and will be forwarded when available eg incomplete pathology test results.(en)
*Details of the nature of supplementary information that is to follow e.g name of laboratory results.(en)
*Local detailed information such as billing requirements.(en)
*Language, transport or other personal requirements to support the patient's attendance or participation in provision of the service.(en)
*Identification of the service requested. This is often coded with an external terminology.(en)

*The status of the request for service as indicated by the requester. Status is used to denote whether this is the initial request, or a follow-up request to change or provide supplementary information.(en)
*A list of people or organisation who should receive copies of any communication.(en)
*Structured detail defining the service requested eg CLUSTER archetype specifying the specific catheter that is to be inserted.(en)
*A detailed narrative description of the service requested.(en)
*Details about the healthcare provider or organisation requesting the service.(en)
*Details about the healthcare provider or organisation receiving the request for service.(en)
*The latest date that is acceptable for the service to be completed.(en)
*Activity regarding a referral from a clinician, or self-referral by a patient, for the patient to receive a specific service, advice or care from an expert healthcare provider.(en)
*Activity regarding a referral from a clinician, or self-referral by a patient, for the patient to receive a specific service, advice or care from an expert healthcare provider.!(en)
*Appointment for a healthcare provider service has been made.(en)
*The healthcare provider has provided the service.(en)
*All service activities have been completed and person returned for ongoing care.(en)
*The referral has been ceased before the service has been completed.(en)
*The planned referral for a service has been cancelled prior to commencement.(en)
*The referral has been suspended without completion.(en)
*Identification of the clinical service to be/being carried out. This is often coded with an external terminology.(en)
*Reason for activity, for example reason referral was stopped early or reason referral was performed.(en)
*Type of service to be carried out or being carried out.(en)
*The local ID assigned to the order by the healthcare provider or organisation requesting the service. This is also referred to as Placer Order Identifier.(en)
*Details about the healthcare provider or organisation requesting the service.(en)
*The ID assigned to the order by the healthcare provider or organisation receiving the request for referral. This is also referred to as Filler Order Identifier.(en)
*Details about the healthcare provider or organisation receiving the request for referral.(en)
*The total number of services to be undertaken.(en)
*The sequence of a particular clinical service.(en)
*The referral has expired before the referral episode has been completed.(en)
*The service was scheduled but not provided.(en)
Документ, отправляемый из одного медицинского учреждения или организации в другую с целью получить консультацию, медицинское обслуживание или осуществить перевод во взрослое отделение.
*For example: Local hospital departmental information or additional metadata to align with FHIR or CIMI equivalents.(en)
Дополнительная информация, требуемая для описания контекстуальных деталей или для установления соответствия с прочими референсными моделями/потоками данных
